Greatest Moments is a greatest hits compilation by British band Culture Club. It was released in the UK on 9 November 1998, and went platinum in the UK, reaching #15 in the album charts. The album also contains three solo Boy George tracks.  The album includes the greatest hits released from the band, spanning from their debut album (1982's Kissing to Be Clever), to their most recent single in 1998. There is also a limited edition bonus disc called VH1 Storytellers Live, recorded live on 2 May 1998 at Sony Studios, New York.  The only single taken from the album is "I Just Wanna Be Loved" which managed to reach #4 in the singles chart..
